In terms of application, the agriculture segment is expected to hold a significant share of the market as farmers continue to rely on acaricides to protect their crops from harmful mites and ticks. The use of acaricides in crop protection has become essential to ensure a healthy yield and safeguard against potential damage caused by pest infestations. Additionally, the animal husbandry segment is also driving market growth as livestock owners seek effective solutions to manage pests that affect the health and productivity of their animals.

The market can be segmented based on the mode of application, with spray applications witnessing substantial growth due to their ease of use and effectiveness in pest control. The convenience and efficiency offered by spray applications make them a popular choice among farmers and pest control operators. Moreover, technological advancements in formulation techniques are enabling the development of safer and more efficient acaricides with reduced environmental impact. This trend towards sustainable pest control solutions is gaining traction in the market as consumers and regulatory bodies increasingly prioritize environmental stewardship.

